== 歷史 ==
[[File:Bob_Woodward.jpg|thumb]]而聞名。]]
爲了吸引年輕讀者，《華盛頓郵報》於2017年2月17日正式在{{lang|en|[[Snapchat|Snapchat]]}}的“發現”平臺（{{lang|en|Snapchat Discover}}）上綫，並在當日第一次公佈此標語，之後才將之加至網站及紙版報名之下。該報通訊總監夏尼·喬治（{{lang|en|Shani George}}）稱標語在正式啓用前已在公司内部流傳多年<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/the-washington-post-introduces-its-new-slogan/|title=Washington Post sells itself to readership with new slogan|last=Bat|first=John|date=2017-02-22|website=[[CBS新聞|CBS新聞]]|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227150010/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/the-washington-post-introduces-its-new-slogan/|archive-date=2020-02-27|access-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

“民主死於黑暗”是《郵報》140年歷史以來首個正式采用的標語<ref name=":1" />，且根據該報，此標語因調查記者[[鮑勃·伍德華|鮑勃·伍德華]]而開始普及<ref name=":0" />。2007年，伍德華在一篇報道中使用此句批判政府的保密作業（{{lang|en|government secrecy}}）<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2017/02/15-classic-metal-albums-whose-titles-are-less-dark-than-the-washington-posts-new-motto.html|title=15 Metal Albums Whose Titles Are Less Dark Than the Washington Post's New Motto|last=Oremus|first=Will|date=2017-02-22|website={{le|Slate (雜志)|Slate (magazine)|Slate 雜志}}|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223034742/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2017/02/15-classic-metal-albums-whose-titles-are-less-dark-than-the-washington-posts-new-motto.html|archive-date=2020-02-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年，伍德華在一次大會上介紹其關於[[水門案|水門案]]的著作《總統的最後人馬》（{{Lang|en|The Last of the President's Men}}）時，談及了此句標語。《華盛頓郵報》老闆[[傑佛瑞·貝佐斯|傑佛瑞·貝佐斯]]出席了前述大會，後在2016年的一次訪問中引用此標語。然而，伍德華强調自己非標語的作者，其真正出處應為一起關於[[美國憲法第一修正案|美國憲法第一修正案]]訴訟案的法官判詞，而此法官据信為[[美國聯邦法官|巡迴法官]]{{le|戴蒙·凯斯|Damon Keith}}。《郵報》在[[唐納·川普|特朗普]]上臺之際推出新標語被外界解讀成對其頻頻攻擊媒體的回應，唯該報否認，且稱早在特朗普贏下[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美國總統選舉]]的[[2016年美國總統選舉共和黨初選|共和黨初選]]前就已經決定啓用官方標語，並由一小群報館員工開會集思廣益，最後從500多條標語中選擇了“民主死於黑暗”<ref name=":1" />。

此句標語亦出現在《華盛頓郵報》[[第五十三届超級碗|2019年超級盃]]的{{le|超級盃廣告|Super Bowl commercials|廣告}}結尾部分。這是《郵報》第一次製作超級盃廣告，並由[[湯姆·漢克|湯姆·漢克]]配音<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeff-bezos-responds-washington-post-super-bowl-commercial-1182282|title=Washington Post Debuts Super Bowl Ad Narrated by Tom Hanks: "Democracy Dies in Darkness"|last=Beresford|first=Trilby|date=|website=[[好萊塢報導|好萊塢報導]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227150006/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jeff-bezos-responds-washington-post-super-bowl-commercial-1182282|archive-date=2020-02-27|access-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://adage.com/video/washington-post-democracy-dies-darkness|title=Washington Post "Democracy Dies in Darkness"|last=|first=|date=2019-01-26|website=[[廣告時代|廣告時代]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227150007/https://adage.com/video/washington-post-democracy-dies-darkness|archive-date=2020-02-27|access-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 反響 ==
《華盛頓郵報》公佈標語后在網上引起了討論<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newser.com/story/238786/washington-post-rolls-out-ominous-new-slogan.html|title=''Washington Post'' Rolls Out Ominous New Slogan|last=Quinn|first=Rob|date=2017-02-23|website={{le|Newser|Newser}}|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190707063700/https://www.newser.com/story/238786/washington-post-rolls-out-ominous-new-slogan.html|archive-date=2019-07-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>。有隸屬其他媒體機構的作家在[[推特|推特]]上嘲笑此句標語，而[[非盈利|非盈利性]]新聞編輯組織{{lang|en|[[ProPublica|ProPublica]]}}則稱標語“棒極了”<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/media/320619-the-washington-post-democracy-dies-in-darkness|title=The Washington Post: 'Democracy dies in darkness'|last=Lejeune|first=Tristan|date=2017-02-22|website=[[國會山報|國會山報]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227155857/https://thehill.com/homenews/media/320619-the-washington-post-democracy-dies-in-darkness|archive-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。網路雜志《{{lang|en|{{le|Slate (雜志)|Slate (magazine)|Slate}}}}》認爲標語“比起[[日報|日報]]標語，更適合成爲末日預言家的口頭禪”，還將它與15張[[重金屬音樂|重金屬]]專輯名稱作對比，稱這些專輯名稱比起《郵報》所采標語“更不黑暗”<ref name=":2" />。該報公佈新標語后，[[梅里厄姆-韋伯斯特|梅里厄姆-韋伯斯特]]在綫詞典上對“民主”（{{lang|en|democracy}}）一詞的搜尋次數隨即飆升<ref name=":3" />。

《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》[[總編輯|執行總編]]{{le|迪恩·巴奎|Dean Baquet}}覺得這句標語“聽起來像是下一部[[蝙蝠俠系列電影|《蝙蝠俠》電影]]的名稱”<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://adage.com/article/special-report-sxsw/failing-york-times-editor-psychoanalyzes-trump-grades-wapo-slogan-sxsw/308255|title='Failing New York Times' Editor Psychoanalyzes Trump, Grades WaPo Slogan at SXSW|last=Ives|first=Nat|date=2017-03-12|website=[[廣告時代|廣告時代]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227162706/https://adage.com/article/special-report-sxsw/failing-york-times-editor-psychoanalyzes-trump-grades-wapo-slogan-sxsw/308255|archive-date=2020-02-27|access-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>，而記者{{le|傑克·謝弗|Jack Shafer}}則稱標語相當“嚴酷”<ref>{{cite tweet|user=jackshafer|number=834167619183845378|date=2017-02-22|title="Democracy Dies in Darkness" is kinda heavy-handed for a newspaper motto.|author=Jack Shafer}}</ref>。[[史提芬·荷伯|史提芬·荷伯]]在其節目《[[荷伯報到|荷伯報到]]》中笑稱該報正式進入了[[哥德次文化|哥德時期]]，而特朗普很可能要等到《{{le|福克斯與朋友們|Fox & Friends}}》晨間節目報道這項消息時才會知曉<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/donald-trump-stephen-colbert-washington-post-slogan-democracy-dies-darkness-1201947472/|title=Stephen Colbert Wonders If Donald Trump Will Get WaPo's "Democracy Dies In Darkness" Message|last=de Moraes|first=Lisa|date=2017-02-23|website=[[Deadline_Hollywood|Deadline Hollywood]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227155858/https://deadline.com/2017/02/donald-trump-stephen-colbert-washington-post-slogan-democracy-dies-darkness-1201947472/|archive-date=2020-02-27|access-date=2020-02-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

